Steps for generating automatic email notification flow for any condition like Approved, Rejected, Submitted.

1. Navigate to Manage Page.
2. Navigate to Scripts.
3. Click +Script.
4. Populate the Name of the script.
5. Select Action for the type then click Save.
6. Enable the script by clicking the enable control.
7. Click the newly created script.
8. Create a new Email Template for the approved notification email using the action script. And create a script for the function to call the email.
9. Again, navigate to Manage Page.
10. Navigate to Actions.
11. Create New Action.
12. Populate the Name and Label. Choose Action Script for the Type. In the Script dropdown, select the appropriate script for the actions.
13. Again, navigate to Manage Page.
14. Create New Triggers.
15. In the General tab. Populate the Name. In the objective dropdown, select Entity Creation and Entity Modification. And for the Execution type select In background.
16. Navigate to Conditions tab. Click Add definition and choose Asset (M.Asset). Then add the conditions that was seen in the image below for the approve notification email.
17. Navigate to Actions tab. Click add action and select the script that you created in Step 3.
18. Click Save and close.
19. Enable the enable notifications.
20. Trigger the action script by creating an asset in Create navigation bar. Then click submit for approval for the asset. Go to Review navigation bar and approved the asset.

